[SN]TITLE[SN]
Northern Ireland manufacturing sales and exports rise

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Manufacturing firms in Northern Ireland had sales estimated at £18.1bn last year, a 3.2% annual increase.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Sales to Great Britain reached their highest ever level, up by 2.2% to £8.2bn.
The recovery in sales to the Republic of Ireland also continued, up almost 10% to £1.6bn.
Sales to the Republic had declined sharply during its long economic downturn.
Exports to the rest of the European Union (excluding the Republic of Ireland) also saw a big rise last year, up 16% to £1.5bn.
Sales to other world markets rose by 4.8% to £3.1bn
The only market to see a fall was within Northern Ireland, where sales decreased by 1% to £3.7bn
